      <txt c="X" s="1" y="210" x="360">Gases</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="1" y="345" x="265">Liquids</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="1" y="345" x="450">Noise</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="1" y="490" x="175">Heating</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="1" y="490" x="355">Chemicals</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="1" y="490" x="525">Vibrations</txt>
    </texts>
    <soundTexts>
      <sndTxt>In the daily work onboard you may be exposed to various hazardous sources that may affect your health. This can be caused by cargo related substances which vary in the different cargos and trades and substances that are present in the environment onboard most ships and which are related to routine operations and maintenance procedures.</sndTxt>
      <sndTxt>Such hazardous sources are:</sndTxt>
      <sndTxt>Gases</sndTxt>
      <sndTxt>Liquids</sndTxt>
      <sndTxt> Noise</sndTxt>
      <sndTxt>Heating</sndTxt>
      <sndTxt>Chemicals</sndTxt>
      <sndTxt>Vibrations</sndTxt>
    </soundTexts>
  </page>
